{
  "stem": "15197.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I look more like a Christian girl, which helped me later on also to survive and to do certain work helping and assist other Jews in danger.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a child, it meant more security, to be more able to move around my Polish neighbors.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Although we didn't have too close contact with them, but, nevertheless, we were part of the Polish society.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And to be able to speak fluent Polish-- and I did speak fluent Polish, although I went to a Yiddish school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, nevertheless, felt more free being able to mingle among the Poles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was, I would say, the most important ingredient of looking as a Polish girl as a child, yes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To comprehend, to understand, and to feel, very early.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As long as I remember my childhood, I knew right away that I am Jewish and what certain things to expect from hooligans or from Poles which are antisemitic or they don't like Jews or even to beat them up in front of my eyes.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So these kind of experiences I had daily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, personally, I didn't encounter any specific things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The same thing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father also didn't look exactly Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my little brother, my mother, they did look different.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, more Semitic outlooks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And very often he came home crying that the boys beat him up because they called him Zyd, Zyd, Zyd.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had it every days, this kind of incident.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We are talking the time before the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because during the war, when the war started in 1939, things changed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the war started, the bombardment started over Warsaw, I remember we were in the basement and my father want to quiet us down because we were afraid.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
